properties.description: From Putney Cross to Putney Park Lane, this self guided walk includes a wealth of significant buildings in a variety of uses past and present, churches, pubs, even the site of WWII bomb damage.

properties.name: Self-guided Architecture Walk - Roehampton Lane
properties.description: This self guided walk combines contemporary architecture with some historic survivals in Roehampton Village, via the famous Alton Estate, Roehampton University campus and Dover House Estate. Don’t forget to do the quiz!

properties.name: Self-guided Architecture Walk - Putney Embankment
properties.description: This walk takes you Thames-side, up to the Lower Richmond Road, back to the famous Boathouses and to the site of a pest house, all just 5 miles from Hyde Park Corner!

properties.name: Self-guided Architecture Walk - Putney High Street to the River Wandle
properties.description: This walk (approx 1 mile) takes you from St Mary’s Church along commercial and residential developments on the south bank of the Thames and through Wandsworth Park ending at the mouth of the River Wandle.

properties.name: Holborn House
properties.description: A redevelopment of Holborn’s community centre improving and increasing facilities  -  the space has been designed by Stirling prize nominated 6a architects and includes a public artwork for the building, created by artist Cargh Thuring

properties.name: East Croydon Community Organisation
properties.description: Find out just what Napoleon had to do with East Croydon and where DH Lawrence lived when he published his first novels. The East Croydon history walk will combine historical research with personal reminiscence.

properties.name: South Norwood Library
properties.description: The purpose-built library is a fine example of brutalist architecture. Built by Hugh Lea, Borough Architect for Croydon, in 1968 the main volume shows miesian influence with an abundance of natural light, interrupted by a concrete cuboid.

properties.name: Brandon Centre
properties.description: West Kentish Town Conservation Area. Brandon Cadbury, (of the famous philanthropic chocolatiers) was so impressed with our founder and young peoples services he donated our building. As a thank you, we named the charity after him in 1984.

properties.name: Enfield To Fork - Edmonton Green Shopping Centre
properties.description: The Museum of Enfield is this year bringing its temporary exhibition to you! “From Enfield to Fork” explores the borough’s history and relationship with food, from Roman Enfield to Market Gardening.

properties.name: Kempton Steam Museum
properties.description: 1920s water pumping station comprising of several architectural styles. Interior retains original steam pumping machinery and historic electrical equipment.

properties.name: Baker Street Complex
properties.description: In 1863, Baker Street was one of the stations on the world's first subterranean metro line. The Metropolitan Railway developed the area around the station to incorporate offices and even residential flats. This tour explores that history.

properties.name: Enfield Chase Walk
properties.description: The walk follows the London Loop footpath through Trent Park and along the Salmons Brook valley through the historical area of Enfield Chase, a former royal hunting forest.

properties.name: 38 Grosvenor Square
properties.description: A beautiful Mayfair town house c 1727 original to the Square. Transformed 1776 by John Johnson for Duke of Dorset; magnificent staircase, lavish ‘Adamesque’ entertaining suite. Mid-C19 Italianate front by Thomas Cundy.

properties.name: A tour of Victorian Bromley
properties.description: A virtual tour that tells the story of Bromley's phenomenal growth in the late 19thC using many Victorian photos to fade in over the modern view to show how the town progressed from a rural market town to suburb in about 20 yrs.

properties.name: A virtual visit to Bromley Palace and Park
properties.description: A Georgian Palace built in 1776 for the Bishops of Rochester. Enlarged and improved by Victorian entrepreneur Coles Child from 1842.  The building and its adjoining park was taken over Bromley Council in 1983

properties.name: Barts Pathology Museum, Queen Mary University of London
properties.description: Barts Pathology Museum is based in the grounds of St Bartholomews Hospital at West Smithfield and houses over 4,000 medical specimens on display over 3 mezzanine levels of the Victorian museum.

properties.name: Modern Architecture in Blackheath walk
properties.description: Architect Ana Sutherland will lead a guided tour of the Cator Estate, covering Eric Lyons' Span estates and unique modernist homes designed by architects Patrick Gwynne, Peter Moro and Walter Greaves.

properties.name: Dreamings collage art exhibition
properties.description: A collage art exhibition. Every day except Monday and Tuesday. A talk "Why Collage?" on Sunday evening at 7, followed by a Q&A and an art raffle for charity

properties.name: Studio Flox
properties.description: Studio Flox at Watermans Art Centre is a combined arts centre. It is located in Brentford, England alongside the banks of the River Thames overlooking Kew Gardens in West London, England

properties.name: Woolwich Heritage Action Zone
properties.description: Come and pick up a self-guided tour of Woolwich, learn more about the Woolwich Heritage Action Zone and 'Meet the Collection', a chance to see some of the collection from the Borough's Museum and Archive collection.

properties.name: Surbiton Queen of the Suburbs
properties.description: Join us for an interesting and informative walk around Surbiton with our experienced guide. Find out why Surbiton was called the Queen of the suburbs and plenty more.

properties.name: Self-guided Old Malden Walk
properties.description: The walk is around Old Malden and covers residential developments within the district. Different styles of suburban architecture includes a selection of modernist housing. There are also historic buildings and other places of interest.

properties.name: Ealing Centre and North
properties.description: Walk led by Ealing Civic Society members, Jenny Gadsby and Josette Bishop. The walk will cover Ealing north of Uxbridge Road. Circumstances permitting, it will include a tea stop in the garden of one of the walk leaders.

properties.name: Ealing South Walk
properties.description: This is an attractive walk through Ealing south of Uxbridge Road. It passes Sir John Soane's Pitzhanger Manor, Ealing Studios and many attractive Georgian and early Victorian streets of Ealing's early development.

properties.name: Sculpture Wars Guided Walk
properties.description: A two-hour guided walk focusing on the great debate currently surrounding statues and monuments. The route will highlight some of the more contentious sculptures in Westminster's corridors of power.

properties.name: 23 Sedgeford Road
properties.description: Completely carbon neutral terraced house following a retrofit solar and air source heat pump installation. Existing radiators, double glazing and roof / loft insulation.

properties.name: The Steamship Project Space
properties.description: With a sculpture garden, performance art in the attic and live music in the bowels of The Steamship, built in the heart of Docklands 1885, the resident artists show how the area has transformed and how they've transformed the former pub.

properties.name: Writing's on the Wall
properties.description: 'The Writing's on the Wall' - a celebration of the street art of East London. Join Mr Londoner, aka former museum director and Blue Badge guide Antony Robbins, to discover the best street art in Shoreditch and beyond.

properties.name: Shepherds Bush Baptist Tabernacle WW1 Hall
properties.description: The Tabernacle Memorial Hall is nestled behind the Tabernacle Church on Shepherds Bush road just off the green. Used as an office space for many years, it has been refurbished and restored into a complimentary health and wellbeing centre.

properties.name: Valence Library
properties.description: Single storey building, officially opened on 30th January 1937 and designed by the Borough’s Engineer & Surveyor F.C. Lloyd.

properties.name: DLR Underline Discovery Sessions
properties.description: DLR Underline Discovery Sessions covers a series of events for all ages focused on exploring the spaces under the DLR on the Isle of Dogs, with activities exploring the area's architecture, heritage and the public realm.

properties.name: Medieval to Millennial
properties.description: Join Blue Badge Guide Sue Grayson Ford to discover the treasures inside Enfield’s medieval parish church, and hear the stories behind many other listed buildings before visiting Enfield Chase and the New River, dating from 1613.

properties.name: Watermans
properties.description: Watermans is a purpose-built combined arts centre comprising a 120-seat cinema, 239-seat theatre, gallery, studios and public spaces. It is brutalist in style in a stunning riverside location.

properties.name: Verity-Jane Keefe, Living Together: The Becontree Collection Billboards
properties.description: A walk across Becontree to view a new series of artworks installed on billboards & roadside locations, sharing some of the objects collected as part of Keefe’s long term project, Living Together, across the estate in its centenary year.

properties.name: The Brentford Gallery
properties.description: Johnson's Island is an artist's community, set on an island on the Grand Union Canal in West London. It is home to a thriving creative community.

properties.name: Blackfriars Estate 150 year anniversary and Peabody history tour
properties.description:
Join us for the 150 year anniversary of our Blackfriars Estate. We'll be running tours Saturday 4 September 2021 from 12.15 – 12.45pm, and 1.45 – 2.15pm.

The community event will run from 12pm - 3pm with speeches at 1pm.

properties.name: Morley College North Kensington
properties.description: Originally built as a school over 4 floors in 1.2 acres of land with an East/West aspect. Steel Frame building with block wall and brick finish.

properties.name: Wellbeing Walk: South Kensington
properties.description: Our walking tour takes inspiration from the streets of South Kensington to explore practical ways to support wellbeing and find pools of calm in the midst of London's buzz and bustle.

properties.name: 33 Genotin Road
properties.description: Modern build concrete structure, glass exterior, 4 storeys plus a basement.  These are now totally used by Microsoft Ltd (previously Metaswitch Networks Ltd) as offices for up to 500 employees.

properties.name: Points of view: Understanding London’s townscape
properties.description: Following architect Gordon Cullen’s ideas of townscape and concentrating on postwar commercial development in the City of London, explore the aesthetic and legislative background to buildings, streets and spaces close to St Paul’s Cathedral

properties.name: Reuse, repurpose, reimagine: Buildings beyond their original identity
properties.description: This walking tour will look at examples of how buildings have been altered to suit new uses. The tour considers what different scenarios lie behind this process of change and the design creativity that can emerge as a result

properties.name: Reuse and redevelopment: A walk in changing Southall
properties.description: This walk through the most diverse of Ealing’s towns will consider the impact of development on the urban fabric and its communities.

properties.name: Greenwich: Big picture, local focus
properties.description: This walk will celebrate some of the famous parts of Greenwich but also look at recent local housing and buildings -- some controversial, some celebrated, as well as streets that are packed with small scale historical gems.

properties.name: Golden Lane and Barbican Architecture Walking Tour
properties.description: The walk, led by architectural historian Billy Reading, will explore the Golden Lane and Barbican estates, designed by architects Chamberlin, Powell & Bon and have witnessed a rollercoaster ride of changing public opinion over the decades

properties.name: Eco Show Home
properties.description: Waltham Forest Council has transformed a Victorian terrace into an Eco Home to showcase best practice retrofitting to be more carbon friendly. Features home improvements that reduce carbon footprint and help tackle the climate emergency.

properties.name: Marylebone Village: Home to The Howard de Walden Estate
properties.description: This fun and engaging walking tour led by expert guide Mike Althorpe - an urban historian, architectural researcher, educator and story teller - will explore the architecture and history of this urban village.

properties.name: The Mysterious Black Tudors - Family Trail
properties.description: Celebrate Open House Festival 2021 with this fun and interactive family event about Britain's forgotten history of the Black Tudors.

properties.name: Open City Film: The Lea Navigation Canal
properties.description: Follows one of the most socially, architecturally and historically diverse parts of London. Part of a 3 part series, exploring the role of wellbeing and architecture around East London kindly supported by Allies & Morrison.

properties.name: Open City Film: Core Landscapes
properties.description: A community garden space teaching horticultural skills to promote positive wellbeing. Part of a 3 part series, exploring the role of wellbeing and architecture around East London kindly supported by Allies & Morrison

properties.name: Open City Film: Poetics of Experience Series
properties.description: Poetics of Experience is a four-part series in collaboration with architectural poet Lionheart and Grimshaw Architects, exploring the relationship between Architecture and Wellbeing.
